place.name: WRIBBENHALL
place.gazetteerText: WRIBBENHALL, a chapelry in Kidderminster parish, Worcester; at Bewdley r. station, within Bewdley borough, and communicating with Bewdley town by a bridge across the Severn. It was constituted in 1844; and it has a post-office under Bewdley. Pop., 1,057. Houses, 249. There are several well built houses and some gentlemen's seats. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Worcester. Value, £150. Patron, the Vicar of Kidderminster. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
